Road closures will be in place on Sunday due to a planned Police Operation for a protest march along Sea Cliff Bridge.

From 1.45pm to 3.15pm Lawrence Hargrave Dr / Sea Cliff Bridge will be closed in both directions between Paterson Rd, Coalcliff and Clifton School Pde, Clifton.

Motorists should use the M1 / Bulli Pass while closures are in place.

Vehicle access will be maintained for residents in suburbs either side of the bridge along Lawrence Hargrave Dr from Bald Hill to Coalcliff and from Scarborough to Clifton. No through traffic will be permitted.

NSW Police and Traffic Control will be on site managing resident access at closure points.
